fields.title: Love, Rosie
fields.review: Finds the perfect balance between heartbreak and comedy. It is very easy to identify with the main characters whose chemistry truly makes the entire movie. A personal favorite from the very first watch.

fields.title: Senior Year
fields.review: Reaches the highest of comedic highs, but loses a bit of its flair towards the end. Otherwise an enjoyable movie that will keep you entertained the whole way through.

fields.title: Good Will Hunting
fields.review: Near-perfect cinema. Hooks you in the beginning, keeps you tense in the middle, and provides you with the most perfect, satisfactory ending possible.

fields.title: Fractured
fields.review: A psychological thriller that toys with the viewers' emotions and logic. We are constantly forced to judge the main character, but unable to make a definite conclusion until the very end.

fields.title: Twilight
fields.review: Not the greatest piece of cinema. Still an enjoyable film for a nostalgic night.

fields.title: Step Up 2: The Streets
fields.review: One of the most beloved franchise sequels ever, and for good reason.

fields.title: Hacksaw Ridge
fields.review: A brilliant film about a brilliant person. From start to finish it is heartwarming and touching. Shedding a tear or two is not unexpected.
